      "content": "Metronidazole and alcohol are a dangerous combination that can cause severe nausea, vomiting, and even liver damage, so you must avoid alcohol entirely while on this medication.\nEven a \"tiny bit\" of red wine is risky because your body metabolizes the drug slowly, and any alcohol can trigger a toxic reaction.\nStick to water or non-alcoholic drinks tonight and wait until your prescription is fully cleared before enjoying a glass of wine.",
